<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-07T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-07T16:36:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24168: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-07T15:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                            1920—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 5—1:32
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>277. My Chilean and Japanese colleagues have informed me that they
                                are in receipt of telegraphic instructions to proceed in harmony
                                with this Embassy in regard to the situation here.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>